<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-10-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-10-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="421" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d421">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Ambassador <persName type="to">Reid</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-10-20"><hi rend="italic">October 20,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(The Secretary of State sends to Ambassador Reid copy of the note to the
                            British ambassador of October 19. He directs him to urge upon foreign
                            office the considerations which it contains and importance of prompt
                            action to avoid increasing bad feeling among fishermen and possible
                            recurrence of incidents like Fortune Bay affair. Unless action is prompt
                            American vessels will lose fishing season.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>